The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 February is 207,823 (23,952.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 February, there were 10,893 new confirmed cases (1,255.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 January, there were 10,802 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (91 extra cases).
